        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the dough",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix the flour, yeast, salt, and sugar in a bowl. Add the warm milk, eggs, and vanilla and mix to a rough dough. Knead for 8 minutes until smooth. Work in the soft butter and continue kneading for 4 minutes. Cover and leave to rise for 60 minutes until doubled.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Shape and prove",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Divide the dough into 12 equal pieces (about 80 g each). Shape each into a smooth, tight ball by pinching the base. Place on lined trays, cover with oiled cling film, and prove for 45 minutes until puffed and light.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Fry and fill",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oil in a deep saucepan to 175°C. Lower doughnuts in, 3 to 4 at a time, and fry for 2 to 3 minutes per side until evenly deep golden. Remove with a slotted spoon and drain briefly on paper, then roll in caster sugar while still warm. When cool enough to handle, push a piping bag nozzle into the side of each doughnut and pipe in about 2 tablespoons of jam.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
